cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.IT

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper deals with privacy-preserving mechanisms and privacy guarantees. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the role of randomness in the design of privacy-preserving mechanisms. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper discusses the sensitivity of queries and the data-generation distribution. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is relevant as the paper discusses the cost model for privacy-preserving mechanisms and compensation budget. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper proposes a probabilistic calibration of privacy-preserving mechanisms.
